purpose.en-US: Maximize performance of the team. Give regular, direct feedback, and quantify value provided by partners.

en-US: Senior Director of People Team, Team Leaders, Partners

completionDescription.en-US:
1. E-mail from Director of Talent reminds that it is time for process to begin
2. Handoff A - Team Leader and Director of Talent 
3. During a 1on1, the Team Leader and Partner schedule a meeting

Partner-
Prepare a presentation for your Team Leader. It should contain:
    a. Your KRA, each assigned a percentage based on their overall importance in your opinion.
    b. Score the completion of each KRA out of 100, and prep a defense of score for your presentation.

Team Leader-
Prepare Feedback for the partner. Specifically:
    a. Your idea of what score they receive on each one
    b. Exhaustive and specific reasons for score adjustments

4. During meeting, Partner presents their KRA performance to Team Leader, and presents their score
based on completion and quality. Team Leader brings up all issues and possible score adjustment factors during meeting. After meeting they may not make any further adjustments or 
raise more issues. They arrive at a final score out of 100.

5. Where applicable, Partner and Team Leader then schedule meeting with Team Leader's manager
to present results.

en-US:
Measures of Success
1. Performance Review sheet signed by partner, manager, manager manager
2. Improvement from previous review
3. Team Leader has a complete score out of 200

purpose.en-US: To use communication tools consistently and make sure their utility is maximized

en-US: All LL partners, Interns

completionDescription.en-US:
1. Email-
Typical use cases for email are longer messages, messages that do not require reply or conversation. Also, anything HR, legal, or official polocy related should be communicated by email.
Partners are responsible for information received by email

2. WeChat-
Use cases for WeChat, Da Bomm LearningLeaders Group Chat, for example are time sensitive messages.
For example, communicating tardiness, coordinating a meet-ups and outside activities. WeChat is also the
place for cheeky banter, fun announcements, and updates about how our learners are doing at debate
tournaments.

3. Podio Chat-
Use cases for Podio chat are file sharing, in office communications, and 'at work' subject matter.
It should be the preferred method of discussing and collaborating about work. Group chats should be
formed for teams/issues/projects. 
Partners are responsible for information received by Podio.


4. Podio Tasks-
Use case is fairly straightforward. Ask people for help. Delegate things. Be specific, attach necessary files,,
and follow-up with people via Podio message to ensure completion.
Partners are responsible for information received by Podio.

en-US:
1. People receive and act on all communications they are responsible for
2. Using the channels consistently helps people no where to find things and what channels to keep an eye on.
3. Information overload avoided

completionDescription.en-US:
1. Gather and list out all your important dates for the semester. Be as specific as possible.


2. Prepare a short presentation on what your team/role does, and your vision for the semester.

3. Consider your semester KRA, and how they might overlap with other partners' work, these areas
of overlap will provide valuable talking points. For example, if you are designing a new attendance system for coaching sessions, you'll have

purpose.en-US: To provide sufficient time slots for parents to meet with coaches during the three week period of parent coach conferences. To minimize disruption of coach schedules.

completionDescription.en-US:
Completion Checklist
(Please note handoffs if any)

1. Use existing class schedule document, or blank spreadsheet to list current class sessions, coaches and enrollment numbers per session


2. Pick one coach from each session to represent the session and it's students. This will add to number of possible appointments per coach possible appointments per coach, so balance as equitably as possible.

purpose.en-US: This process explains how to arrange a superday interview once the interviewers decide that the candidate should be invited for an in-person interview with the rest of the team

en-US: Senior Director of People Team, Team Members involved in the Super Day

completionDescription.en-US:
1. Senior Director of People team sends an E-mail to the candidate asking if they are available earliest day majority of team is in the office (Within 1 week after the project submission - refer to Recruiting Process Document)

2.Set up team schedule: 
    a. Send candidate CV and date of super day in Podio group chat 
        i. Partners reserve time on first come first serve basis
    b. Send out brief description of intended role to partners 
    c. Schedule will contain interviews with team members (Potential Direct Manager at the end of the day, one with team peer, and one not 
    directly related to the candidate, and one with Michael. Others will go to lunch with candidate)
    d. Breakfast scheduled for next morning to discuss feedback

3. Confirm schedule with candidate 
    a. Send candidate: Schedule, core values PDF, expectations for interview"

4. Send team reminder 24/48 hours in advance 
    a. Add team meetings to calendar 
    b. Create SurveyMonkey for final feedback after the Superday

5. After receiving feedback, if YES, then ask for 9 referrals from the candidate.

en-US: 1. From first contact to starting date in less than two months with clear yes/no

purpose.en-US: This process explains the entire recruitment process for candidates that are interesting in working with LearningLeaders.

en-US: Senior Director of People Team

completionDescription.en-US:
1. The team member referring the candidate sends through the appropriate job description for the candidate via E-mail (Found in Recruting => Files Library)

2. The candidate information is put in the Recruitment => Candidate workspace with all the appropriate categories filled out with contact information by the team member referring the candidate or the people team.

3. Once the proper application documents are received, phone/skype screening is conducted by the people team (Either Senior Director of People Team or Director of HR). The interview notes are uploaded into the candidate workspace

4. After the phone/skype screening, the interviewer indicates thumb up or down on the candidate workspace and updates the status of the hiring process. If YES, the director of people team sends the cultural fit questionnaire using the webform link. The questions will either be input after the interview or before depending on the role. This must be done within 3 days with a 72 hour deadline for the candidate. 

5. After the cultural fit answers are received, the senior director of people team goes over the answers. If the answers lead to a thumbs up, then the senior director of people team connects the candidate to the potential direct manager via E-mail. This must be done within 3 days of receiving the cultural fit questionnaire. 

6. After the potential direct manager completes the interview, the answers to the interview questions along with the questions must be uploaded to the candidate workspace with status updated. The direct manager selects thumb up or down. If YES, the senior director of people team connects the candidate to a team peer via E-mail. This must be done within 3 days, and call arranged within a week.  

7. After the team peer completes the interview, the interview Q&A must be uploaded to the candidate workspace with status update. Team peer selects thumb up or down. If YES, a project/assignment is sent to the candidate by the senior director of people team after discussion with the potential direct manager. This must be done within 3 days, 72 hours given for completion

8. Once the project/assignment is received, the potential direct manager and senior director of people team will go over the submission. If YES, then a survey will be sent to the interviewers to ask whether candidate should be invited to superday.

9. The candidate will be invited to superday (Refer to Superday Interview Process)

en-US:
1. Candidates go through the interview process within the time frame indicated in the process.
2. Candidates that receive high reviews are hired and team member agreement is sent within 2 months after the interview process.

purpose.en-US: Summer Interns can stay in Shanghai legally.

en-US: Director of HR, Senior Director of People Team

completionDescription.en-US:
1. Once the intern candidate signed the Team Member Agreement, the Director of Human Resources is responsible for collect the passport copy for preparing the invitation letter for business visa application.

2. US citizens can apply a multi-entry of 90 days stay F visa.

3. Non-US citizens can only apply a double entry of 30 days stay M visa. I am pretty sure that this does NOT apply to ALL Non-US citizens. Please check other citizens because this limits the summer internship significantly going forward.

4. After the invitation letter is signed by CEO, the director of HR will send the scan copy of it and company business license copy to the applicant. The standard lead time is 4 working days.

5. For some reasons, the applicant can not apply it by him/herself, the travel/visa agent is required. The summer intern is expected to pay upfront for the visa application, and he/she must keep the receipt or record in order to be reimbursed. If the summer intern needs the reimbursement before arrival, he/she will be paid by Alipay.

6. LL will book the flight and hotel for summer interns (non-Chinese) through the travel agent. The summer intern is expected to send through the arrival and return dates based on the Team Member Agreement.

7. LL will pay the stipend to summer interns by cash every Friday.

8. The interns can claim the China visa fee by cash. This will be an alternative for those that are willing to wait until arrival. 

9. LL will book the flight for the interns if they need to leave China for visa run.

en-US: 1. All Summer interns/Summer camp coaches can get the business visa without any issues.

completionDescription.en-US:
1. The Senior Director of People Team gathers SurveyMonkey feedback from the Superday Interview. If the decision is unanimously a HIRE, proceed to Reference Check. If one or more people indicates "NO HIRE", the Senior Director of People Team and Managing Parter will make the ultimate decision whether to proceed or not. 

2. Once the decision of whether to proceed to reference check is made, the Senior Director of People Team reaches out to the candidate to obtain 4 references of their choice. The Senior Director will also let the candidate know that after receiving their choice, LearningLeaders will select 4 references of our choice. 

3. Once the Senior Director of People Team receives the reference choices from the candidate and their contact information, he/she reaches out to the references to arrange a 15 - 20 minute call. 

4. Once the contact information for the LearningLeaders' choice is sent through to the Senior Director of People team, provide the information to the other team member who will be conducting the remaining reference checks and arranges the phone call. Having two people responsible for reference checks will allow the team to compare notes and check for consistency. 

5. The Reference Call time should be scheduled based on the reference's schedule. When scheduling the call, ask for either his/her Skype ID or phone number via E-mail to make sure the call is done smoothly during the scheduled time

6. Prepare a list of questions based on the Reference Call Question Samples Document. Take notes throughout the entire call. (Sample questions attached) 

7. Once the reference calls are completed, the two team members must compare notes and decide whether the offer will be made or not.

purpose.en-US: How to Pitch LearningLeaders in 60 seconds or 6 minutes, depending on the setting.

en-US: LL Partner

completionDescription.en-US:
1. The Problem

Have you ever felt nervous or unsure when speaking to another person or speaking in public?  Most likely, because the majority of people, estimated at over 75%, experience glossophobia - a fear of public speaking.  Public speaking anxiety can lead to serious detrimental effects on ones quality of life, career goals, and personal relationships.  Were here to help anyone who wants to become a more effective communicator, in any language.

At LearningLeaders, our vision is a world where everyone is heard, respected, and understood.

2. Our Solution

Our mission is to empower everyone to lead, delight, and inspire.

Near-term: We have developed a systematic approach through fourteen different public speaking and debate courses offered in our brick-and-mortar LearningCenters, based in Shanghai.

Long-term: A virtual-reality-based communication coaching platform and two-sided marketplace connecting communication coaches and learners from all over the globe.

3. Target Market

Near-term: Shanghai-based parents who value their children communication skill development as a long-term investment.  Its simply the worlds best market for what we do in terms of market size, ability and willingness to pay, and cultural dispositions.  Long-term: Anyone who wants to be heard, respected, and understood.

4. Competition

The education market in China is fragmented, with the largest player capturing approximately 1% of consumer spend.  Within our sub-sector, competition exists in the marketplace and will continue to increase.  Due to the low barrier to entry market conditions, we expect in the future the market will become more and more competitive.  This is great for us, as the market is still small and growing and we need all the help we can get to educate consumers and create demand.

5. Our Team

Our team consists of partners from diverse backgrounds, 25 and growing.  Among our team we have working experience at organizations like Apple, J.P. Morgan, Bank of America, Teach for America, Yale University, private-equity firms, and billion-dollar Chinese technology firms.  We have advanced degree-holders, from Ph.Ds in sociology to J.Ds. and Masters Degrees holders.  Our visiting coaches hail from NYU, UNC, the New York Times, and Yale Law School, among others.  The one commonality we all have is our love of improving the communication skills of others.

6. Financial Summary

In 2017, we grossed nearly 10MM RMB and in 2018 we expect to reach 20MM.  By 2020, with growth of our core programs as well as in the introduction of our Virtual Reality-based public speaking simulator, our top-line revenue is projected to exceed 55MM RMB, at which point we may seek other funding to truly scale our business digitally.

7. Milestones

In 2016, students who train with LearningLeaders coaches won their first national debate championship.  In 2017, students who train with LearningLeaders coaches won 5 of the 6 national tournaments offered and in the sixth they came in second place.  Team China is currently represented by students who train at LearningLeaders.  We have created the best middle school and high school debate teams in the country, without peer.

By February 2018, we have secured three consecutive World Schools Nationals Championships, are defending champions of Public Forum Debate Nationals, and have the top-ranked high-school students at British Parliamentary Debate. Of the three most popular debate styles in the world, our students are the best in the country.

By Fall 2018, we expect to achieve relative financial stability, meaning that we will have 6 months of operating budget banked in cash.  This will allow us to make bigger bets in the future and position the company to more nimbly access market opportunities as they appear.

Last update: 2/28/18

purpose.en-US: Got Beef? Read this Process Guide to resolve the conflict in the smoothest way possible.

en-US: LL Partner

completionDescription.en-US:
At the root of our culture of open feedback at LearningLeaders, we practice observing BEHAVIORS OF OTHERS and then sharing OUR EMOTIONS we feel related to those behaviors.  Neither of these are able to be argued with (provided they are true) and thus it is a simple way to avoid engendering further conflict.  When we deliver constructive feedback and remark about the way anothers actions makes ourselves feel, it creates a totally different atmosphere and conversation than to call someone else, a liar, a cheater, or lazy, for instance.  One is a judgement about the other persons character.  The other is a reflection of ourselves in relation to anothers actions.

So to resolve a conflict in the least violent method possible, reference the below script for a sample of what conflict resolution may sound like when executed effectively.

A: I have a concern Id like to share with you. Is now a good time?
A: The specific facts as I remember them are...
A: This leads me to wonder/think...
A: I feel...
A: The part Ive played in this is...
A: What I specifically want/hope for is...

<>

B: Let me see if I understood you correctly...
B: Is that accurate? Did I miss anything?
B: Is there anything else youd want to share?
B: Have you said everything you feel you need to say?
B: Thank you.

<>

B: My reaction after hearing your concerns/feelings/thoughts are...
B: My response to what you want it...
B: What I want or need from you is...

en-US: Both parties are satisfied with the result and leave the conversation emotionally unscathed.

purpose.en-US: The goal of this process is to ensure candidates are recruited in a given amount of time (Maximum 1.5 - 2 months) in a strategic manner that allows us to evaluate the candidate to the best of our abilities.

en-US: Senior Director of People, DIrector of Human Resources

completionDescription.en-US:
1. For referrals, all candidates are expected to apply through our career website (www.joinlearningleaders.com). Once the application is submitted, the Senior Director of People is responsible for clicking "Application Considered" or "Application Unqualified" based on the resume and content uploaded.

2. Once the application is received, the Associate Director of Partner Recruitment (Senior Director of People or Director of Human Resources until Recruiter's on-boarding completed) conducts a first phone/skype call screening in order to evaluate his/her skills. 

3. If the candidate is able to skip the phone screening process, the Senior Director of People or the Associate Director of Partner Recruitment will speak with the candidate directly for a first round Skype/Face-to-face interview. 

4. The interviewer MUST create a structured interview scorecard before the interview and evaluate all responses based on the interview. Once the interviewer completes the interview, he/she must identify whether the candidate should move to the next step YES/NO and identify hire, enthusiastically hire, or no. 

5. The Associate Director of Partner Recruitment will then send the cultural fit questionnaire for the candidate to respond to. 

6. Once received, the AD of PR will arrange the second round interview with the potential supervisor. 

7. After the second round interview, the AD of PR will be responsible for 1) Sending the written assignment 2) Share information about the open compensation system + range of compensation 3) Visa application process and the requirements of them 4) Timeline. 

8. After the written assignment is received, the candidate will either move to the third interview with Managing Partner (If Senior Role) or conduct a Mock Lesson for a interviewer based on the written assignment and then move to the interview with Managing Partner. 

9. Once the Managing Partner completes the structured interview scorecard with a Hire/Enthusiastically Hire,  the Superday logistics will be coordinated.

title.en-US: How do we give people promotions?

purpose.en-US: To clarify the circumstances in which people can get a promotion.

en-US: Senior Director of People Team

completionDescription.en-US:
WHY? (Do we have performance reviews and promotion procedure?) 

Performance Reviews allow LearningLeaders and supervisors to provide data for why certain actions are taken. The only ethical and fair way to communicate performance to an organization is through evaluation applied to all parties. Additionally, it aligns with our values: 

Prioritize People's Potential: Performance reviews help us hold ourselves and the team accountable. Rewards achievement and prioritizes improvement.

Take No Shortcuts: Provides us with an opportunity to go through an honest and thorough reflection of our work and behavior. 

Embrace the Adventure: Allows us to learn from the feedback. 

Act with Initiative: Gives the team member the opportunity to take initiative to fill the gaps. 

WHAT? (Is the process?) 
A Semi-Annual performance review that incorporate two aspects 1) Achievement through Key Results Areas 2) Performance through 360 Review 
-For Supervisors: A tool to determine 1) strength areas and areas of improvement for each team member 2) career progression and promotion opportunities for each team member 
-For Team Members: A tool to determine 1) his or her own strength areas and areas of improvement 2) his or her own career growth opportunity 

HOW? (Do we determine when we can promote people?) 
    1. A team member continuously performs highly (At least two cycles of performance reviews (165 - 175/200) 
    2. A job opening is advertised internally and externally
    3. A position opens up unexpectedly and needs to fill it from within
    4. A team member acquires a credential that allows them to progress to another level 
    5. A team member has been at LearningLeaders for a certain number of years 

Experience-Based: For every two years, team members receive a compensation raise. 
Performance-Based: Once a team member has been with LearningLeaders for at least one year, he or she is eligible for a promotion after a performance review cycle. 
Opening-Based: If there is an opening for a position internally that is unrelated to the current position, the position will be advertised for internal team members as well. He or she may apply by raising the opportunity to his or her supervisor.  



WHEN? (Can we determine promotions?) - Performance Review Timeline

    By June 1st, 2018: The eight 360 Review evaluators have been selected (Team Members, Supervisor, Chosen, and Random) 
    By June 4th, 2018: 360 Reviews are sent to everyone
    By June 8th, 2018: Team Member KRA Presentation competed for Supervisors
    By June 8th, 2018: All 360 Review Surveys have been submitted 
    By June 13th, 2018: All KRA review evaluation completed by Supervisor 
    By June 15th, 2018: KRA and 360 Review results shared with team members and supervisors 

By June 22nd, 2018: Managers determine who will be eligible for what type of promotion 
    1) Compensation Raise? (Lower => Middle, Middle => Upper) 
    2) Title Raise? (Increase in responsibilities AD => Director Level) 
    3) Move to a different role? 

By June 29th, 2018: Manager has met with Senior Director of People to determine the 1) Title 2) Responsibilities 3) Compensation for the Team Member.

By July 6th, 2018: New Team Member Agreement has been drafted with details on when the promotion will be effective.

By July 13th, 2018: Promotions have been announced to the team with clear reasons to explain WHY

Key Action Items: What should Supervisors do now? 

1. Identify the WHY: Why do you believe that a promotion is necessary for your team this cycle? Is it necessary? 
2. Identify the WHAT: What opportunities are available for your team members? Management responsibilities? Increase in DRI projects? A role on a different team? 
3. Identify the HOW: Begin speaking with team members about the type of responsibilities they are looking to take on. Share the HOW with the team member - what do they need to do to achieve this goal? 
4. Identify the WHEN: When will the team member be able to be promoted? Is the role they want available? If YES, then great! If NO, share that they need to wait for now. Manage expectations.

en-US:
1. Partners know when they are eligible for a promotion. 
2. Team leaders know how to lead the discussion when a partner.
